@startuml
title Cluster Development Workflow with FluxCD

actor Developer
participant "Git Repository" as Git
participant "FluxInstance" as Flux
participant "Kubernetes\nCluster" as K8s

== Current Workflow (Has Pruning Issue) ==

Developer -> Git: 1. Checkout new branch (feature-x)
activate Git

Developer -> Flux: 2. Edit sync: branch master → feature-x
activate Flux
Flux -> Git: Reconcile from feature-x
Git --> Flux: New/updated manifests

Flux -> K8s: 3. Apply new resources
activate K8s
note right of K8s: Resources created\n(e.g., new Deployment)

Developer -> Git: 4. Add/update resources
Git --> Flux: Sync changes
Flux -> K8s: Apply updates

Developer -> Git: 5. Merge feature-x → master
Developer -> Flux: 6. Change sync back to master

Flux -> Git: Reconcile from master
note over Flux,K8s #FFB6C1: ⚠️ PROBLEM: Resources added\nin feature-x but not yet\nin master get PRUNED!
Flux -> K8s: Prune orphaned resources
destroy K8s

deactivate Git
deactivate Flux

@enduml